recipeIngredients:
• Butternut squash, raw, 2 cup(s), cubes, cut into 1-inch pieces (9.9oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ¼ cup(s) (1.4oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, ½ medium, sliced (2.1oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Taco seasoning, 1 tbsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Eggs, 2 large (3.5oz)
  • Instant brown rice, cooked, 4.4 oz(s) (4.4oz)
  • Black beans, canned, ½ cup(s), rinsed (4.2oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, 5 cherry tomato(es), diced (3oz)
  • Baby spinach, 1 cup(s) (0.7oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, ½ cup(s), chopped (0.4oz)
  • Lime, ½ lime(s) (1.2oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Mexican buddha bowl according to recipe instructions below.

Serve one portion of this recipe for lunch and refrigerate the remaining cooked and salad vegetables in separate airtight containers, along with one egg for lunch later this week.

Mexican buddha bowl instructions

Preheat oven 400°F. Place the squash, onion and peppers in a small roasting pan and toss with the olive oil and taco seasoning, mix to coat. Roast for 20 minutes or until vegetables are golden and tender. Meanwhile, cook the eggs in a small saucepan of water for 6 minutes for soft boiled or 8 minutes for hard boiled. Refresh in cold water, peel and cut eggs in half.

Divide the rice into two serving bowls. Divide the squash, onions, peppers, black beans, tomatoes and spinach between the bowls. Top with the egg halves and cilantro leaves. Squeeze over the lime juice to serve.

TIP: To save time, place the squash into microwave-safe dish, add a splash of water, cover and microwave for 2 minutes, check and cook further until squash is soft. Drain water and sprinkle over taco seasoning. Peppers and onion can be added to the bowls raw.
NutritionInfo: Calories343Total Fat10.4 g- Saturated Fat2.4 gCholesterol186 mgSodium814 mgTotal Carbohydrate50.8 g- Dietary Fiber10.9 g- Total Sugars7.7 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein14.5 g

recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Ginger, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Chicken breast, raw, 3 oz(s), cut into ½ inch pieces (3oz)
  • Snow peas, ½ cup(s), ends trimmed (2.8oz)
  • Asparagus, 10 spear(s), (1/2 bunch) (5.3oz)
  • Zucchini, noodles, 2 cup(s) (6.4oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
recipeInstructions:
Heat a large non-stick frying pan or wok on medium-high heat. Add olive oil, garlic, ginger and chicken. Cook for 5-6 minutes or until golden and cooked through.

Add snow peas and asparagus and stir fry for another 1-2 minutes.

Toss in zoodles and cook for 1 minute then turn off heat. Spoon into bowl to serve and season to taste.

TIP: If you have a spiralizer you can prepare zucchini noodles yourself. Add fresh chilli or chilli flakes with the chicken for an extra kick!

recipeIngredients:

  • Cumin, ground, 3 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 3 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Beef top sirloin steak, any grade, very lean, 9 oz(s), cut into strips (9oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, 1 medium, sliced (4.2oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Naked beef fajitas according to recipe instructions below.

Whilst preparing the meat, make salsa by mixing cucumber, tomato, cilantro, lime and pepper in a bowl and set aside.

Once the beef has cooked, place lettuce leaves on a serving plate and spoon one portion of the beef fajita mix inside topping with fresh salsa.

Fold romaine leaves and eat like a taco (be careful of spills!). Alternatively, shred lettuce leaves and enjoy as a salad.

TIP: Place remaining serves of the beef fajita recipe into two airtight containers and refrigerate for use later in the week.

Naked beef fajitas instructions

To make fajita seasoning, in a large bowl, combine olive oil with cumin, garlic and pepper. Add beef strips to bowl and massage seasoning into the strips.

Heat a large non-skillet skillet over medium heat. Add onion and red pepper and cook, stirring until tender. Remove from skillet and set aside.

Increase heat to high and add beef. Cook, stirring for 4 to 5 minutes or until browned. Return vegetables to skillet and stir for a further 1 minute.

Remove from heat and divide the beef into three portions.

recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 1 large (1.8oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Asparagus, 5 spear(s), thinly sliced crossways (2.6oz)
  • Low-fat cottage cheese, 1%, ¼ cup(s) (2oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 2 slice(s) (2.3oz)
  • Fruit, any type, 1 small piece(s) (3.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
In a small bowl, lightly whisk the egg. Season to taste and set aside.

Heat oil in a small, non-stick frying pan on medium-high heat. Add the asparagus and cook for 5 minutes, or until nearly cooked. Add a little water if needed to help them cook through. Remove mixture from the pan, place in a bowl and set aside.

Clean the non-stick frying pan and place it back on medium-high heat. Pour in egg and continue to stir until it is nearly cooked through and light and fluffy. Stir in the cottage cheese. When mixed through, add asparagus back to the pan and gently mix everything together. Remove from heat.

While eggs are cooking, toast bread. Serve toast with scramble on top.

Follow with a piece of fruit of your choice, or save for mid-morning snack.

TIP: You can leave some of the cottage cheese out of the scramble and spread on the toast, before topping with the scrambled egg mixture. Feel free to mix up the vegetables to your liking, or add garlic or chilli when cooking vegetables for some extra flavor.

recipieName: Seared salmon with cucumber & tomato sambal
recipeIngredients:
• Asparagus, 10 spear(s), thinly sliced crossways (5.3oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), to taste
  • Cucumber, 1 medium, diced (7.1oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, 10 cherry tomato(es), halved (6oz)
  • Ginger, minced, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Sweet chili sauce, low-sodium, 1 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Lime, ½ lime(s), juiced (1.2oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, ½ cup(s), chopped (0.4oz)
  • Atlantic salmon, farmed, 6 oz(s), two small fillets of 3 oz each or one large piece, halved (6oz)
  • Baby spinach, 2 cup(s), or arugula (1.3oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Seared salmon with cucumber & tomato sambal using recipe instructions below.

Refrigerate one salmon fillet, spinach, and sambal salad in an airtight container for dinner tomorrow night.

Seared salmon with cucumber & tomato sambal instructions

For the sambal, place the asparagus in a heatproof bowl, cover with boiling water, stand for 3 minutes then drain. Refresh in cold water, drain well. Return to the bowl and stir in the remaining sambal ingredients: cucumber, tomato, ginger, sweet chili sauce, lime, and cilantro.

Lightly rub both sides of the salmon with oil and season to taste.

Heat a non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook salmon 2 to 3 minutes each side or until cooked to your liking.

Arrange the spinach on serving plates. Add salmon and spoon over the sambal.
